- Why?
- I don't know.

5
00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:33.070
Don't be scared.

6
00:00:41.420 --> 00:00:47.100
When I was little and we used to move
all the time, I'd write these notes,

7
00:00:47.130 --> 00:00:49.510
and I would fold them
up really small...

8
00:00:50.590 --> 00:00:54.480
...and I would hide
them in different places,

9
00:00:54.510 --> 00:00:58.680
so that if I ever wanted to go back,
there'd be a piece of me there waiting.

10
00:00:59.680 --> 00:01:02.570
- Did you ever go back?
- No.

11
00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:04.240
See? That's what I'm saying.

12
00:01:04.270 --> 00:01:06.020
'Cause I didn't need to.

13
00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:08.530
What'd they say?

14
00:01:09.610 --> 00:01:13.320
They were just like,
old rhymes and poems.

15
00:01:13.950 --> 00:01:16.240
Things I wanted to
remember about...

16
00:01:17.530 --> 00:01:22.540
...living in that house
or what I liked about it.

17
00:01:25.880 --> 00:01:27.170
Why did you leave?

18
00:01:28.090 --> 00:01:30.710
Why'd you leave
all those houses?

19
00:01:31.510 --> 00:01:33.760
'Cause I didn't have a choice.

